ast.name: conference app
ast.comment: Reads conference data as defined in http://www.conference-publishing.com/ConfEventData-JSON.php.

body.text: This application reads the data for a conference as defined in http://www.conference-publishing.com/ConfEventData-JSON.php. All the data contained in the JSON is stored in `data` and in `records`.
You can use this script as a base to start building your conference application.
For this demo, we download the data from the CHI 2012 conference hosted on Microsoft Research servers. The parser expects valid JSON back.
If the download fails, the previous data will be kept intact.
Use `is cached` to test if you already have the data stored locally. In conference, it is usually the case that participants don't have internet access so caching is very important.
Determines if we have the event data cached already
